  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Productive Use of Electricity by micro and small enterprises in urban and peri-urban Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the project is to facilitate access to electricity by subsidizing 5,000 Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs) in urban and peri-urban areas with preference to women headed small businesses through an output-based aid approach but targeting subsidies in a gender-sensitive and socially inclusive manner. The Project is also intended to have a strong pro-poor focus hence supporting the World Bank-housed Global Partnership on Output Based Aid (GPOBA) and GRZ&#x2019;s central objectives of providing targeted subsidies to basic services.</narrative>
  </description>
